671	  On a proper geometrically connected $k$-curve $C$, Stein factorization gives $\Gamma(C, \struct C) = k$ — finite over $k$. Combined with the constant-sheaf / global-sections adjunction, this provides a producer instance for \lstinline{IsHModuleHomFinite k C (toModuleKSheaf C)}, queued for iter-044+. Together with iter-040's H${}^{>0}$ vanishing class (whose producer is multi-iteration via Čech-vs-derived comparison + affine Čech vanishing), the iter-043 wholespace H${}^0$ class closes the *producible* affine-input scaffolding for the LES finite-length transport. Iter-041's "all affines" H${}^0$ class stays in scope as a user-suppliable hypothesis but is unlikely to be instantiated on a proper curve.
